events.title: Pakistan Floods, Spring/Summer 2015
events.description: Heavy rainfall has resulted in flash flooding in northern and central Pakistan from the early spring through the monsoon in July and August.

events.title: Colombia: Floods and Landslides, Spring 2015
events.description: Flooding, windstorms and landslides affected more than 20,000 people in Colombia in April 2015. The rainy season in the southern and western departments had a particularly strong impact in the Amazonas department near the Peruvian and Brazilian border.

events.title: Rwanda: Floods and Landslides
events.description: On 3 April 2015, heavy rainfall caused flooding and landslides in Nyamasheke and Rubavu districts in Rwanda's Western Province.

events.title: Calbuco Volcano, Chile
events.description: Calbuco volcano, located in the province of Llanquihue, state of Los Lagos, southern Chile, erupted on 22 Apr 2015.

events.title: Mud Lake Complex Fire
events.description: The Mud Lake Complex is comprised of several fires caused by lightning strikes on Big Cypress National Preserve both north and south of Interstate 75 (Alligator Alley).

events.title: Tajikistan: Floods and Mudslides
events.description: Prolonged torrential rains caused a number of floods and mudslides between 11 and 13 May 2015 in Khatlon province and Hoit administrative center of the Rasht valley of Tajikistan.

events.title: Alaska Heat Wave, May 2015
events.description: In the third week of May, it was warmer in Fairbanks, Alaska, than in Washington, D.C. The small town of Eagle, Alaska, was hotter on May 23 than it has been on any day in Houston or Dallas this year. In what has become a frequent occurrence in the past few years, temperature profiles in North America appeared to be upside down.

events.title: Sea of Marmara Phytoplankton Bloom
events.description: Freshened surface water and abundant nutrients lead to an explosion of algae in the inland sea.

events.title: Wolf Volcano
events.description: After 33 years of inactivity, Wolf volcano in the Galapagos has reawakened.

events.title: Fires in Northern Canada
events.description: Fires burned in the Northwest Territories, spreading smoke across the region.

events.title: Democratic Republic of the Congo Fires, June 2015
events.titleShort: Democratic Republic of the Congo Fires
events.description: In June 2015, seasonal fires dotted central Africa.

events.title: Guadalupe Fire
events.description: http://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/4268/

events.title: Ghana: Floods - June 2015
events.description: Heavy rains starting at the beginning of June 2015 have left most parts of Ghana's capital Accra, its suburbs and other cities flooded.

events.title: Saddle Fire, California
events.description: The lightning-caused Saddle Fire began on Tuesday, June 9, 2015.

events.title: Chisana River 2 Fire, Alaska
events.description: The Chisana River 2 wildfire, burning 25 miles West of Beaver Creek, Yukon, Canada started on the Wrangell-St. Elias National Park and Preserve by a lightning strike June 9.

events.title: Buckskin Fire, Oregon
events.description: The Buckskin Fire began on June 11 and is burning in the Rogue River – Siskiyou National Forest, southwest of Cave Junction, OR, in an area previously burnt by the 2002 Biscuit Fire.

events.title: Sockeye Fire, Alaska
events.description: The fast-moving Sockeye Fire has grown very quickly and is expected to continue to grow due to hot, dry weather.

events.title: Moore Fire, New Mexico
events.description: The lightning-caused Moore Fire was detected on June 16, 2015 and is located seven miles east of Gila Hot Springs in the Gila Wilderness, New Mexico.

events.title: Tropical Storm Bill
events.description: Tropical Storm Bill, the second named storm of the 2015 hurricane season, pushed ashore near Matagorda Island, Texas, on June 16, 2015.

events.title: Healy Lake and Michigan Creek Fires, Alaska
events.titleShort: Healy Lake and Michigan Creek Fires, Alaska
events.description: The Healy Lake Fire was started by lightning on June 16, 2015. The Michigan Creek Fire started on June 17, approximately 9-10 miles northeast of Healy Lake. Dry fuels and strong winds caused the fires to rapidly grow in size.

events.title: Lake Fire, California
events.description: The Lake Fire was reported just before 4:00 pm on June 17, 2015.

events.title: Tanana Area Fires, Alaska
events.description: The Tanana Area Fires include Spicer Creek, Bering Creek, Harper Bend, Moose Point, and Kokrine fires, all of natural causes.

events.title: Washington Fire, California
events.description: The lightning caused Washington Fire started 45 miles south of Carson City Nevada on June 19. The extreme fire activity being witnessed is primarily due to strong erratic winds and severe drought conditions.

events.title: Queen Charlotte Sound, Canada, Phytoplankton Bloom
events.titleShort: Queen Charlotte Sound, Canada, Phytoplankton Bloom

events.title: Tok Area Fires, Alaska
events.description: The Tetlin HIlls, Long Lake, and Moose Creek fires were started by lightning strikes south of Tok, Alaska on June 20.

events.title: Blair Fire, Alaska
events.description: The Blair fire started on June 20 by lightning. The fire started on State Forestry land, then moved on to military land.

events.title: Anaconda Creek Fire, Alaska
events.description: The Anaconda Creek Fire was started by lightning on June 20.

events.title: Tozitna Fire, Alaska
events.description: The Tozitna fire was detected in the early morning hours of Monday, June 20th, approximately fourteen miles northwest of Tanana, Alaska. By Tuesday morning, June 21st, conservative estimates were that the fire had grown to 25,000 acres.

events.title: Rex Complex Fires, Alaska
events.description: This complex of fires includes both the Kobi Fire which is west of the Parks Highway, and the Fish Creek Fire which is on the east side. The fire is creating it's own weather with thunderstorm cells in the area.

events.title: Bangladesh: Floods and Landslides, Summer 2015
events.description: Since June 24, torrential rains have set off flash floods and landslides in the low-lying areas in the south-eastern districts of Cox’ Bazar, Bandarban and Chittagong. Tropical Cyclone Komen hit on July 31, affecting more than 1.5 million people across these same coastal districts.

events.title: Costa Rica Flooding, June 2015
events.description: Since late June 2015 heavy and constant rains have affected various locations in central and eastern Costa Rica, causing damage and forcing evacuations in the provinces of Limón, Heredia and Cartago.

events.title: Hansen Fire, Florida
events.description: The Hansen wildfire was ignited naturally by lightning in Big Cypress National Preserve on June 26, 2015.

events.title: Wildfires in Alberta and Saskatchewan
events.description: Dozens of uncontrolled fires are burning in northern Alberta and Saskatchewan.

events.title: Dust storm over Libya and Egypt
events.titleShort: Dust storm over Libya and Egypt

events.title: Sleepy Hollow Fire, Washington
events.description: The Sleepy Hollow Fire, located near Wenatchee, Washington, started in the early afternoon of June 28 and spread quickly in the 100+ degree temperatures and windy conditions.

events.title: Venezuela Floods, July 2015
events.description: Since 29 June 2015, heavy rainfalls in the south and southwest of the country have caused river overflows and subsequent floodings, including in the states of Apure, Táchira, Mérida and Zulia.

events.title: Corner Creek Fire, Oregon
events.description: The Corner Creek Fire was ignited by lightning on June 29.

events.title: Raung Volcano, Indonesia, July-August 2015
events.description: One of the most active volcanoes on the Indonesian island of Java spewed fresh ash and gases in early July 2015.

events.title: Alex Camp Road Fire, Montana
events.description: The lightning-caused Alex Camp Road Fire was first reported July 2.

events.title: Twenty-One Mile Grade Fire, Washington
events.description: The human-caused Twenty-One Mile Grade Fire began on the afternoon of July 2.

events.title: 231 Complex Fire, Washington
events.description: The 231 Complex includes the 231 Fire and the Little Spokane Fire. The 231 Fire started on July 3 and the Little Spokane Fire started on July 6. The cause of both fires are under investigation.

events.title: Cape Horn Fire, Idaho
events.description: The Cape Horn Fire was first reported on July 5. The cause is not known at this time.

events.title: Last Dance Fire, Florida
events.description: A lightning strike on July 9, 2015 started a wildfire in the northern section of Loxahatchee National Wildlife Refuge.

events.title: Blue Creek Fire, Washington
events.description: The Blue Creek Fire started on Monday, July 20 at approximately 12:30 p.m. local time. The cause is currently under investigation.

events.title: Lake Erie Algal Bloom
events.description: A bloom of algae continues to grow in Lake Erie and surrounding waters.

events.title: Reynolds Creek Fire, Montana
events.description: The Reynolds Creek fire was reported in the afternoon of July 21 and has prompted evacuations within Glacier National Park.

events.title: Willow Fire, California
events.description: The Willow Fire started on July 25 and is in steep and rugged terrain within the Sierra National Forest.

events.title: Stouts Fire, Oregon
events.description: The Stouts Fire was reported on Thursday, July 30, 2015 on forestlands protected by the Douglas Forest Protective Association (DFPA). The Stouts Fire has displayed extreme fire conditions and is growing quickly.

events.title: Northeast India Floods, August 2015
events.description: Heavy monsoon rains in the tea and oil-rich state of Assam have caused burgeoning rivers, including the mighty Brahmaputra, to burst their banks.

events.title: Dust Storm over Southern Egypt
events.description: A wall of dust rolled north from Sudan into southern Egypt.

events.title: Sucker Creek Fire, Montana
events.description: The lightning-caused Sucker Creek Fire is in very rugged, steep terrain and burning in a stand of tree snags.

events.title: Explosion at Tianjin, China
events.description: Fires associated with a massive explosion in Tianjin, China, sent dark smoke drifting east and southeast.

events.title: Spotted Eagle Fire - Family Peak Complex, Montana
events.titleShort: Spotted Eagle Fire - Family Peak Complex, Montana

events.title: West Fork Fish Creek Fire, Montana
events.titleShort: West Fork Fish Creek Fire, Montana

events.title: Indonesia Fires, Fall 2015
events.description: Smoke poured from seasonal fires in Indonesia in the fall of 2015.

events.title: Hurricane Danny
events.description: Tropical storm Danny has strengthened to become the first hurricane of the 2015 Atlantic hurricane season.

events.title: Dust storms in Middle East
events.description: During early September 2015, a cyclone-shaped wall of dust and a series of dust storms swept across the Middle East and Persian Gulf.

events.title: Valley Fire, California
events.description: The Valley Fire in northern California has already consumed 70,000 acres and over 600 homes and structures.

events.title: South Carolina Floods
events.description: Heavy rainfall from a combination of tropical moisture and a non-tropical system resulted in heavy flooding in South Carolina.

events.title: Somalia Floods, October 2015
events.description: The Deyr 2015 rainy season started well in many parts of Somalia and has been increasing in space and intensity over the last few days within the Juba and Shabelle river basins both in Somalia and in the Ethiopian highlands.

events.title: Iraq Flooding, October-November 2015
events.description: Heavy rains in late October caused flooding in and around Baghdad, as surface drainage is minimal.

events.title: Cyclone Chapala
events.description: After forming in the Arabian Sea, Cyclone Chapala headed for the Arabian Peninsula.

events.title: Esperance Fires, Australia
events.description: Bush fires have damaged power lines, burned 133,000 hectares, and destroyed two homes.
